.title Help: Volume Manager Package
ABOUT THIS PACKAGE
The Volume Manager builds virtual devices called volumes on top
of physical disks. Volumes are accessed by file system in the same
way physical disk partitions would be accessed. Volumes and their
virtual components can be manipulated in a varity of ways to
optimize performance, to perform disk mirroring, disk spanning. etc.

EXITING THE PACKAGE SELECTION MENU
Press <Enter> to enter your selections and to return to the
Install Menu.

EXITING HELP
Press <Esc> to return to the Package Selection menu.
